<paragraph id="3735368BD12BFFC2FF3CAB6E4FBFD540" blockId="120.[128,654,1289,1759]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">
DEFINITION: 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FEE3AB6D4D6CD518" box="[323,570,1290,1313]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Heloderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horridum">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FEE3AB6D4D6CD518" box="[323,570,1290,1313]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Heloderma horridum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FDF2AB6B4E05D506" class="Reptilia" family="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" genus="Lowesaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="matthewi">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FDF2AB6B4E05D506" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Lowesaurus matthewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FED0AB4F4DD0D506" authorityName="Hoffstetter" authorityYear="1957" box="[368,646,1320,1343]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Eurheloderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gallicum">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FED0AB4F4DD0D506" box="[368,646,1320,1343]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Eurheloderma gallicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and all descendants of their last common ancestor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7F906500D12BFFC2FF3CABE74DD8D6E6" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3735368BD12BFFC2FF3CABE74DD8D6E6" blockId="120.[128,654,1289,1759]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">
DIAGNOSIS: The node here referred to as 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FF20ABC74E6DD58F" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[128,315,1440,1462]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Helodermatidae</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed by seven unambiguous synapomorphies in the current analysis. These are 37(1) prefrontal-postfrontal/postorbitofrontal contact present, 57(1) frontals rhomboid in dorsal view, 77(3) absence of a pineal foramen, 115(1) absence of palatine teeth, 118(2) absence of pterygoid teeth (reversed in some 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FE0FA8084FFAD69A" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Heloderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="suspectum">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FE0FA8084FFAD69A" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Heloderma suspectum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 182(1) absence of a dentary shelf (fig. 38E), and 220(1) presence of a distinct venom groove in the dentary teeth (fig. 38E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7F906500D12BFFC3FD7AAEB44F96D147" lastPageId="121" lastPageNumber="122" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3735368BD12BFFC2FD7AAEB44C1AD214" blockId="120.[701,1228,211,1759]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">
COMMENTS: 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FCDDAEB24B6FD0D2" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[893,1081,213,235]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Helodermatidae</taxonomicName>
as defined here generally follows common usage (
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FD65AF684B7BD11C" author="McDowell, S. B., Jr &amp; C. M. Bogert" box="[709,1069,271,293]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="1 - 142" refId="ref95300" refString="McDowell, S. B., Jr, and C. M. Bogert. 1954. The systematic position of Lanthanotus borneensis, and the affinities of the anguinomorphan lizards. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 105 (1): 1 - 142." type="journal article" year="1954">McDowell and Bogert, 1954</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FBE1AF774CF0D17B" author="Bogert, C. M. &amp; R. M. Del Campo" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="1 - 238" refId="ref84194" refString="Bogert, C. M., and R. M. Del Campo. 1956. The Gila monster and its allies: the relationships, habits, and behavior of the lizards of the family Helodermatidae. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 109 (1): 1 - 238." type="journal article" year="1956">Bogert and Del Campo, 1956</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FC1DAF4B4B27D17B" author="Yatkola, D. A." box="[957,1137,300,322]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref102577" refString="Yatkola, D. A. 1976. Fossil Heloderma (Reptilia, Helodermatidae). University of Kansas Museum of Natural History Occasional Papers 51: 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="1976">Yatkola, 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FB28AF4A4DA1D166" author="Estes, R." pageId="120" pageNumber="121" refId="ref87654" refString="Estes, R. 1983. Sauria terrestria, Amphisbaenia. New York: Gustav Fischer Verlag, 249 pp." type="book" year="1983">Estes, 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FCADAF2D4CA8D166" author="Norell, M. A. &amp; M. C. McKenna &amp; M. J. Novacek" box="[781,1022,330,352]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref96369" refString="Norell, M. A., M. C. McKenna, and M. J. Novacek. 1992. Estesia mongoliensis, a new fossil varanoid from the Late Cretaceous Barun Goyot Formation of Mongolia. American Museum Novitates 3045: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1992">Norell et al., 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FBB3AF2D4DA3D144" author="Gao, K. - Q. &amp; R. C. Fox" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref89287" refString="Gao, K. - Q., and R. C. Fox. 1996. Taxonomy, and evolution of Late Cretaceous lizards (Reptilia: Squamata) from western Canada. Bulletin of Carnegie Museum of Natural History 33: 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1996">Gao and Fox, 1996</bibRefCitation>
) and is similar to the usage of 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FBC3AF004C66D1A3" author="Pregill, G. K. &amp; J. A. Gauthier &amp; H. W. Greene" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="167 - 202" refId="ref97643" refString="Pregill, G. K., J. A. Gauthier, and H. W. Greene. 1986. The evolution of helodermatid squamates, with description of a new taxon and an overview of Varanoidea. Transactions of the San Diego Society of Natural History 21: 167 - 202." type="journal article" year="1986">Pregill et al. (1986)</bibRefCitation>
who first applied this term to a node on a cladogram. This differs from the usage of some subsequent authors who prefer a crown based application of 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FBB0AFBB4B9DD1CB" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[1040,1227,476,498]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Helodermatidae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FD65AF9E4CB2D236" author="Norell, M. A. &amp; K. - Q. Gao" box="[709,996,505,527]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref96317" refString="Norell, M. A., and K. - Q. Gao. 1997. Braincase and phylogenetic relationships of Estesia mongoliensis from the Late Cretaceous of the Gobi Desert, and the recognition of a new clade of lizards. American Museum Novitates 3211: 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="1997">Norell and Gao, 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FC59AF9D4DA1D215" author="Gao, K. - Q. &amp; M. A. Norell" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="1 - 51" refId="ref89425" refString="Gao, K. - Q., and M. A. Norell. 1998. Taxonomic revision of Carusia (Reptilia: Squamata) from the Late Cretaceous of the Gobi Desert, and phylogenetic relationships of anguimorphan lizards. American Museum Novitates 3230: 1 - 51." type="journal article" year="1998">Gao and Norell, 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FCA4AC704C16D214" author="Gao, K. - Q. &amp; M. A. Norell" box="[772,832,535,557]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref89476" refString="Gao, K. - Q., and M. A. Norell. 2000. Taxonomic composition, and systematics of Late Cretaceous lizard assemblages from Ukhaa Tolgod and adjacent localities, Mongolian Gobi Desert. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 249: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="2000">2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3735368BD12BFFC2FD7BAC524C21D51E" blockId="120.[701,1228,211,1759]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FD7BAC524C3BD272" author="Estes, R." box="[731,877,565,587]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" refId="ref87654" refString="Estes, R. 1983. Sauria terrestria, Amphisbaenia. New York: Gustav Fischer Verlag, 249 pp." type="book" year="1983">Estes (1983)</bibRefCitation>
tentatively included 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FBD1AC534C10D250" baseAuthorityName="Estes" baseAuthorityYear="1964" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Paraderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bogerti">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FBD1AC534C10D250" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Paraderma bogerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his treatment of 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FBE0AC354DAFD2BF" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Helodermatidae</taxonomicName>
, citing plesiomorphic characteristics and the then-forthcoming study by 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FBC3ACEA4C7BD2F9" author="Pregill, G. K. &amp; J. A. Gauthier &amp; H. W. Greene" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="167 - 202" refId="ref97643" refString="Pregill, G. K., J. A. Gauthier, and H. W. Greene. 1986. The evolution of helodermatid squamates, with description of a new taxon and an overview of Varanoidea. Transactions of the San Diego Society of Natural History 21: 167 - 202." type="journal article" year="1986">Pregill et al. (1986)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FC98ACCC4C92D2F9" author="Estes, R." box="[824,964,682,704]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" refId="ref87654" refString="Estes, R. 1983. Sauria terrestria, Amphisbaenia. New York: Gustav Fischer Verlag, 249 pp." type="book" year="1983">Estes (1983)</bibRefCitation>
further cautioned that a parietal he had referred to 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FBA8ACAF4DABD2C2" authority="(Estes, 1964)" baseAuthorityName="Estes" baseAuthorityYear="1964" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Paraderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bogerti">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FBA8ACAF4B2ED2E7" box="[1032,1144,711,734]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">P. bogerti</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FB27ACAF4DA3D2C2" author="Estes, R." pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="1 - 180" refId="ref87547" refString="Estes, R. 1964. Fossil vertebrates from the Late Cretaceous Lance Formation eastern Wyoming. University of California Publications in Geological Sciences 49: 1 - 180." type="journal article" year="1964">Estes, 1964</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
might be that of 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FC45AC834C56D321" authorityName="Gilmore" authorityYear="1928" class="Reptilia" family="Varanidae" genus="Palaeosaniwa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canadensis">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FC45AC834C56D321" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Palaeosaniwa canadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the parietal of 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FB92AD644B9DD321" authorityName="Gilmore" authorityYear="1928" box="[1074,1227,769,792]" class="Reptilia" family="Varanidae" genus="Palaeosaniwa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canadensis">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FB92AD644B9DD321" box="[1074,1227,769,792]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">P. canadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is inconsistent with that morphology and the parietal is here tentatively considered to belong to 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FCE4AD3D4CE8D349" baseAuthorityName="Estes" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[836,958,857,880]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Paraderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bogerti">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FCE4AD3D4CE8D349" box="[836,958,857,880]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">P. bogerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD12BFFC2FC76AD3D4B9AD349" author="Pregill, G. K. &amp; J. A. Gauthier &amp; H. W. Greene" box="[982,1228,858,880]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" pagination="167 - 202" refId="ref97643" refString="Pregill, G. K., J. A. Gauthier, and H. W. Greene. 1986. The evolution of helodermatid squamates, with description of a new taxon and an overview of Varanoidea. Transactions of the San Diego Society of Natural History 21: 167 - 202." type="journal article" year="1986">Pregill et al. (1986)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FC89AD114CF1D3B4" box="[809,935,886,909]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Heloderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FC89AD114CF1D3B4" box="[809,935,886,909]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Heloderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FC18AD1F4B68D3B4" box="[952,1086,888,909]" class="Reptilia" family="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" genus="Lowesaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FC18AD1F4B68D3B4" box="[952,1086,888,909]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Lowesaurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FBF0AD114B31D3B4" bold="true" box="[1104,1127,886,909]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">5</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FBC7AD114DB6D393" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Heloderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FBC7AD114DB6D393" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Heloderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FD59ADF34C37D392" box="[761,865,916,939]" class="Reptilia" family="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" genus="Lowesaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="matthewi">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FD59ADF34C37D392" box="[761,865,916,939]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">matthewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FCD9ADF34BDED392" authorityName="Hoffstetter" authorityYear="1957" box="[889,1160,916,939]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Eurheloderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gallicum">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FCD9ADF34BDED392" box="[889,1160,916,939]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Eurheloderma gallicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FD1DADD64CCED3F1" baseAuthorityName="Estes" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[701,920,945,968]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Paraderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bogerti">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FD1DADD64CCED3F1" box="[701,920,945,968]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Paraderma bogerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in their 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FBA9ADD54B9ED3F1" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[1033,1224,946,968]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Helodermatidae</taxonomicName>
. The latter usage is consistent with that of Estes et al., who defined it as a stem including ‘‘ 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FD6CAA6E4C1CD419" box="[716,842,1033,1056]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Heloderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FD6CAA6E4C1CD419" box="[716,842,1033,1056]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Heloderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and all organisms sharing a more recent common ancestor with this taxon than with any other extant organisms,’’ (Estes et al., 1988: 228). Given the phylogenetic topology presented here (figs. 54E, 55E) and a crown-based definition for 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FBC4AAFB4C4BD4F6" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Helodermatidae</taxonomicName>
, helodermatids would be a subclade of 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FD4AAAB14C3ED4D4" box="[746,872,1238,1261]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Heloderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FD4AAAB14C3ED4D4" box="[746,872,1238,1261]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Heloderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Consequently, maintaining 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FD1DAA934C2ED533" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[701,888,1268,1290]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Helodermatidae</taxonomicName>
in a traditional sense is advocated here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3735368BD12BFFC3FD7BAB484F96D147" blockId="120.[701,1228,211,1759]" lastBlockId="121.[93,619,213,382]" lastPageId="121" lastPageNumber="122" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">
The current application of 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FBE0AB484DA0D55A" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Helodermatidae</taxonomicName>
to the node specified above is beneficial given that all of the anchor taxa for the name were originally described as helodermatids (as opposed to ‘‘necrosaurids’’/‘‘parasaniwids’’; e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FCFCABA64B6AD5E1" baseAuthorityName="Estes" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[860,1084,1473,1496]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Paraderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bogerti">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FCFCABA64B6AD5E1" box="[860,1084,1473,1496]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Paraderma bogerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FB2CABA64CD5D5CC" authorityName="Borsuk-Bialynicka" authorityYear="1984" class="Reptilia" family="Anguimorpha incertae sedis" genus="Gobiderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pulchrum">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FB2CABA64CD5D5CC" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Gobiderma pulchrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and are retained as a monophyletic group in all of the principle trees recovered by this study (see also Auge´, 2003). 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FCB0A8504CABD674" box="[784,1021,1590,1613]" class="Reptilia" family="Varanoidea incertae sedis" genus="Estesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mongoliensis">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FCB0A8504CABD674" box="[784,1021,1590,1613]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Estesia mongoliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is variable in its placement in the current analysis. Different principle trees place it as the sister-taxon to 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FD1DA8E84C1CD69C" box="[701,842,1678,1701]" class="Reptilia" family="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" genus="Lowesaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="matthewi">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FD1DA8E84C1CD69C" box="[701,842,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">L. matthewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FCFDA8E84CB4D69C" authorityName="Hoffstetter" authorityYear="1957" box="[861,994,1678,1701]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Eurheloderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gallicum">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FCFDA8E84CB4D69C" box="[861,994,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">E. gallicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FB84A8E84BE7D69C" box="[1060,1201,1678,1701]" class="Reptilia" family="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" genus="Lowesaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="matthewi">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FB84A8E84BE7D69C" box="[1060,1201,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">L. matthewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FD1DA8CC4C6DD6FB" box="[701,827,1707,1730]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Heloderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12BFFC2FD1DA8CC4C6DD6FB" box="[701,827,1707,1730]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Heloderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade, or as the sister-taxon to 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12BFFC2FD1DA8AE4C2ED6E6" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[701,888,1737,1759]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Helodermatidae</taxonomicName>
as defined here. This phylo- genetic hypothesis owes, in part, to the relative quality of known 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12AFFC3FE08AE944D66D131" authorityName="Hoffstetter" authorityYear="1957" box="[424,560,241,264]" class="Reptilia" family="Helodermatidae" genus="Eurheloderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gallicum">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12AFFC3FE08AE944D66D131" box="[424,560,241,264]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">E. gallicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12AFFC3FFFDAF774FA5D11F" box="[93,243,271,294]" class="Reptilia" family="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" genus="Lowesaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidosauria (awaiting allocation)" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="matthewi">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12AFFC3FFFDAF774FA5D11F" box="[93,243,271,294]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">L. matthewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D12AFFC3FEC6AF774D72D11F" box="[358,548,271,294]" class="Reptilia" family="Varanoidea incertae sedis" genus="Estesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mongoliensis">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D12AFFC3FEC6AF774D72D11F" box="[358,548,271,294]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">E. mongoliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may or may not be a helodermatid as the name is defined here, but it is certainly a monstersaur.
</paragraph>
